🧠 Basic DevOps Interview Questions & Answers

1. What is DevOps?
➡️ DevOps is a culture and set of practices that combine software development (Dev) and IT operations (Ops).
The goal is to shorten the system development life cycle and deliver high-quality software continuously.


---

2. What are the key benefits of DevOps?
✅ Faster software delivery
✅ Improved collaboration between teams
✅ Better quality and reliability
✅ Continuous feedback and improvement
✅ Reduced deployment failures


---

3. What are the main phases of a DevOps lifecycle?

1. Plan – Project planning using Jira, Azure Boards


2. Code – Writing and managing code using Git


3. Build – Using Maven, Gradle, Jenkins


4. Test – Using Selenium, JUnit, etc.


5. Release – Using Jenkins, Docker, Helm


6. Deploy – Using Kubernetes, Ansible


7. Operate – Using monitoring tools like Prometheus, Grafana


8. Monitor – Feedback and continuous improvement



